One of the best habits if you're prone to binging, is planning your meals the day before. When you know what you're going to eat, and it's something nutritious and satisfying that you took the time to plan, you're less likely to just overeat whatever you see when you're hungry. Not drinking your calories helps a lot too. Sugary drinks make you crave unhealthy foods with them, on top of just being awfully unhealthy on their own. There are a lot of better alternatives.

Edit: Also, to curb your appetite when you're not actually hungry but food might just be around and tempting, brushing your teeth and/or drinking peppermint or green tea (or any kind of unsweetened tea that you typically wouldn't have food with) can be especially helpful, I've found.
